    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Canthium oblongum are fever, malaria, and skin infections, which are often treated with a decoction of the plant's leaves. Diarrhea and dysentery are also effectively managed with this treatment, as the plant's properties help to reduce inflammation and soothe the digestive tract. Inflammation, rheumatism, and arthritis are alleviated through the plant's analgesic and anti-inflammatory effects, which also aid in the treatment of cholera and gastroenteritis. Additionally, Canthium oblongum has been used to treat respiratory issues, such as cough, and fungal infections, including those caused by insect bites. The plant's properties also help to manage hypertension, diabetes, skin irritation, eczema, typhoid, influenza, and other conditions, including cholera and malaria, which are often caused by bacterial or parasitic infections.",
