    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Canthium oblongum are infusion, tincture, decoction, tea, and salve, which are utilized due to its medicinal properties including antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, and antimicrobial activities. The infusion of Canthium oblongum is prepared by steeping the plant material in hot water to extract its bioactive compounds, which are then consumed as a beverage. The tincture is a concentrated liquid extract prepared by soaking the plant material in a solvent such as ethanol or glycerin, allowing for easy dosing and storage. Decoction is a preparation method involving boiling the plant material in water to release its bioactive compounds, often used for roots and bark. A salve is a topical preparation made by infusing the plant material in oil, typically coconut or olive oil, allowing for the application of its medicinal properties to skin wounds and conditions.",
