    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Canthium oblongum improperly include nausea and abdominal pain due to the excessive intake of its alkaloids, which can cause irritation and inflammation in the gastrointestinal tract. Fatigue may also be experienced as a result of the alkaloids' interference with the body's normal metabolic processes, leading to a decrease in energy levels. Diarrhea can occur due to the laxative effect of the alkaloids, which can cause excessive water loss and electrolyte imbalance in the body. These side effects are more likely to occur when Canthium oblongum is consumed in excessive amounts or without proper medical supervision. Prolonged or repeated exposure to these alkaloids can exacerbate these side effects and potentially lead to more serious health complications.",
    "uses": "Canthium oblongum is known to have various medicinal uses, including the treatment of fever, headache, and rheumatism. The plant's leaves are traditionally used to relieve pain and reduce inflammation. It is also used to treat skin conditions such as eczema and acne. Additionally, Canthium oblongum has been reported to have antimicrobial properties, which make it effective against certain types of infections. The plant's roots and stems are sometimes used to treat digestive issues and other health problems.",
    "taxonomy": "Canthium oblongum belongs to the family Rubiaceae. It is a species of flowering plant in the Rubiaceae family. The genus Canthium is part of the Rubiaceae family and comprises around 20 species of flowering plants. These plants are typically found in tropical and subtropical regions. The classification of Canthium oblongum places it within the Rubiaceae family, which includes many other species of flowering plants.",
    "benefits": "Canthium oblongum is a plant species that has been traditionally used for medicinal purposes in various parts of the world. The leaves of Canthium oblongum are said to have anti-inflammatory properties, which may help in reducing swelling and pain. Additionally, the plant is believed to possess antimicrobial properties, making it effective against certain types of bacteria and fungi. Its extracts are also thought to have antioxidant properties, which can help protect the body from oxidative stress and damage. Further research is needed to confirm the health benefits of Canthium oblongum and its potential applications in modern medicine.",
    "parts": "Canthium oblongum is a plant species with reported medicinal properties. The leaves and roots of Canthium oblongum are used in traditional medicine in various regions. Traditionally, the plant's leaves and roots are used to treat fever, cough, and other health conditions. The plant's roots are said to have anti-inflammatory properties, making it useful for treating skin conditions. In addition, the plant is believed to have antioxidant properties, which can help protect against cell damage.",
    "intro": "Canthium oblongum, also known as the 'Pitipiti' or 'Pitipiti tree', is a medicinal plant species native to tropical Africa. The plant has been traditionally used to treat various health conditions, including fever, rheumatism, and skin infections, due to its antimicrobial, anti-inflammatory, and antipyretic properties. The bioactive constituents of Canthium oblongum include flavonoids, alkaloids, and terpenoids, which are responsible for its medicinal properties. In traditional herbal medicine, Canthium oblongum is often prepared as a decoction or infusion, as well as being used in the form of a paste or ointment to treat various ailments."
